Gateways don't have a prefix length, this should be removed.

I see difference in routing table bases on prefix, don't you think this needed to route based given prefix?

Kernel IPv6 routing table there is difference based on prefix value.
Destination                                 Next Hop                             Flags Metric Ref    Use Iface
::/64                                       2002:803:15f:345::1                     UGH   1024   1        0 eth0


without prefix if we add route

::/0                                        2003:403:15f:345::1                     UGH   1024   1        0 eth0

Hi William 

looking at configuration looks like we need to have prefix length for each route
otherwise it adds route as host route (UGH), which may not work as gateway for all ip address in that prefix range  

The destination prefix of the route. Possibly followed by a slash and the prefix length. If omitted, a full-length host route is assumed.

Gateways don't have a prefix length other than 0, just drop this.
